result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Cases called at 9:00 AM: 21CF481, 21CF925, 21CF1147, 21CF1242, 21CF1282, 21CF1287, 21CM909, 21CF89.
Defendant David E.M. Young appeared by video, in custody from Stanley Correctional.  Attorney Karl A Schmidt in court for David E.M. Young.  Attorney Angela Beranek in court for State of Wisconsin.
Agreement has been reached. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
21CF481: Defendant pleads Guilty to Count 1: Operating a Motor Vehicle Without Owner's Consent; Repeater, Count 2: Possession of Methamphetamine; Repeater, Count 3: Bail Jumping; Repeater.
21CF1242: Defendant pleads Guilty to Count 1: Possession of Methamphetamine.
21CF1282: Defendant pleads Guilty to Count 1: Felony Bail Jumping. Defendant makes a statement to the Court.
Sentence is Withheld and the Defendant is placed on 3 Years of Probation with the following conditions:
180 Days of Jail (on 21CF481 Count 1) stayed pending further order of the Court. No contact with A.J., E.T., Woodmans, Fleet Farm, Scheels.
No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting.  
Defendant not to consume/use/possess any illegal drugs/non-prescribed medications/controlled substances or drug paraphernalia. 
Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
Restitution in the amount of $582.20 plus the 10% surcharge for a total of $640.42.
Court Costs/surcharges including one warrant fee. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
Defendant is granted 3 days credit in 21CF481 and 5 days credit in 21CF1242. Remaining charges are dismissed and read in.
